    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>wedges</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-pulled-pork-pizza-with-garlic-dip/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Put a large baking tray (or two) in the oven to heat up (this will stop your pizza bottom[s] from going soggy!)</p><p>Add your <strong>tomato paste </strong>to a bowl with your <strong>BBQ sauce</strong> and 5 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [7 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [10 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>BBQ base</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-pulled-pork-pizza-with-garlic-dip/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain your <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-pulled-pork-pizza-with-garlic-dip/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>BBQ pulled pork</strong> to a clean chopping board and chop into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Transfer the <strong>chopped BBQ pork</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>juices</strong> and mix it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>BBQ pork</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-pulled-pork-pizza-with-garlic-dip/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the heated tray[s] from the oven and add your <strong>pizza base[s] </strong>then divide the <strong>BBQ base</strong> between the <strong>pizza base[s]</strong> and spread it evenly all over with the back of a spoon, then top with the <strong>BBQ pork</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>torn\u00a0mozzarella </strong>and put\u00a0the tray[s] in the oven for 12-15 min or until the cheese has melted and the base is crispy \u2013 this is your <strong>BBQ pork pizza</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 2 or more? Make sure the pizzas don't overlap on the tray to avoid raw dough!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-pulled-pork-pizza-with-garlic-dip/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (not a big garlic fan? Try using less!) with your<strong> mayo</strong>,<strong> dried oregano</strong> and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>garlic dip</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-pulled-pork-pizza-with-garlic-dip/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-pulled-pork-pizza-with-garlic-dip/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top the <strong>BBQ pork pizza</strong> with the <strong>sliced spring onion </strong>and serve with the <strong>wedges </strong>and<strong> garlic dip</strong>\u00a0to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
